Manchester City winger, Raheem Sterling, has admitted he could return to Liverpool in the future. Sterling, during an Instagram Q&A, expressed his undying love for the Reds. When he was asked if he would return to Liverpool one day, the England international replied: “Would I ever go back to Liverpool? To be honest with you I love Liverpool. “Don’t get it twisted, they are always in my heart. It’s a team that has done a lot for me growing up so…” Sterling moved from Liverpool to City in 2015 for £49million. Ever since the transfer, he has always received a red hot reception from fans.